Ask HN: Service that blocks new inbound emails from unapproved senders
text:
I had seen a service in the past where, if you're emailing me for the first time, it asks you to do one of two things:

1) verify that you know me by answering a simple question

2) make a donation to a cause I care about so your email goes through

I'm pretty diligent about unsubscribing from all the crummy business newsletters I somehow get signed up for, but am looking for something a bit more aggressive.

In short: I'm looking for a service to keep out all emails except for the few senders I care about

Ask HN: Should members receive karma credit for long nested comment threads?
text:
I've noticed low-karma comments can often trigger long comment discussions. These comments should receive transitive karma. e.g. a comment with 50 sub-comments should receive subcomment-karma-factor X 50.

It could incentivize members who write stimulating yet "less conforming" comments

There are many sub-branches of Econ. I don't know which is my favorite. I do enjoy material on behavioral economics that i've read.

I've read books like freakonomics, superfreakonimics, voltage effect, the why axis, and thinking fast and slow.

Would love to dive deep into in. Looking for the following recommendations in all branches of Econ:

* MasterClasses * Youtube or course material * Books

Thanks
